00:15:07,722 --> 00:15:10,889
He's indeed what you call a 100% "Edoite".

302
00:15:10,889 --> 00:15:14,122
I guess I'll go check after all!

303
00:15:14,122 --> 00:15:16,622
-Genta! -Excuse me.

304
00:15:20,604 --> 00:15:23,304
"Evaluation Room" -What the hell's going on?

305
00:15:23,304 --> 00:15:25,604
Gathering us in a place like this.

306
00:15:25,604 --> 00:15:28,404
We finished interrogation a while ago, didn't we?

307
00:15:28,404 --> 00:15:30,909
Don't tell us you figured out who the culprit is?

308
00:15:30,909 --> 00:15:32,604
Oh, well...

309
00:15:32,604 --> 00:15:34,104
I want to confirm with you once again

310
00:15:34,104 --> 00:15:37,404
what was written on the paper.

311
00:15:37,404 --> 00:15:40,704
It's "Hapyakuichi". I wrote "801".

312
00:15:40,704 --> 00:15:42,404
It was "Shakuhachi" (Bamboo fluter).

313
00:15:42,404 --> 00:15:44,304
It was "Ippin" (First class).

314
00:15:44,304 --> 00:15:45,504
Huh?

315
00:15:45,504 --> 00:15:47,404
What're you guys talking about?

316
00:15:47,404 --> 00:15:49,704
A number was written on it, wasn't there?

317
00:15:49,704 --> 00:15:51,604
Yes, I thought it was a number too.

318
00:15:51,604 --> 00:15:53,504
Don't be silly!

319
00:15:53,504 --> 00:15:56,104
There couldn't be a simpler kanji!

320
00:15:56,104 --> 00:16:00,404
Maybe they were all shown different papers after all.

321
00:16:00,404 --> 00:16:02,941
-Yeah. -I'm pretty sure

322
00:16:03,104 --> 00:16:05,204
that this was what was written on the paper.

323
00:16:05,204 --> 00:16:07,904
Right, it was that character!

324
00:16:07,904 --> 00:16:10,949
See? It's "hapyakuichi"!

325
00:16:11,104 --> 00:16:14,304
But if you turn it upside down,

326
00:16:14,304 --> 00:16:16,504
it can be read, "shakuhachi", can't it?

327
00:16:16,504 --> 00:16:19,504
Then, when you said "shakuhachi",

328
00:16:19,504 --> 00:16:22,004
you actually meant "hyakuhachi"?

329
00:16:22,004 --> 00:16:22,961
Huh?

330
00:16:22,961 --> 00:16:25,704
Yes, that's why I said "shakuhachi".

331
00:16:25,704 --> 00:16:27,704
What the hell are you talking about?

332
00:16:27,704 --> 00:16:28,967
Let me see it!

333
00:16:28,967 --> 00:16:31,704
If you turn the word "ip" up this way,

334
00:16:31,704 --> 00:16:35,504
it's read "ippin" meaning the best!

335
00:16:35,504 --> 00:16:37,904
It's true that it could be read that way.

336
00:16:37,904 --> 00:16:41,004
But it's difficult to read "pin" as the kanji "thing".

337
00:16:41,004 --> 00:16:43,304
Well, it can't be helped!

338
00:16:43,304 --> 00:16:44,983
Because that character "pin"

339
00:16:45,204 --> 00:16:49,004
is written in one stroke, a habit of the writer.

340
00:16:49,004 --> 00:16:50,004
It's hard to tell if it's part of the sentence,

341
00:16:50,004 --> 00:16:52,991
unless you look really carefully and are used to seeing it.

342
00:16:52,991 --> 00:16:55,404
It's really difficult to read it "pin" meaning thing.

343
00:16:55,404 --> 00:16:58,997
Isn't that right, the head of the robber group?

344
00:17:00,999 --> 00:17:02,804
Come to think of it, the kanji character "pin" in the letter

345
00:17:02,804 --> 00:17:04,304
that was left behind by the group of robbers saying

346
00:17:04,304 --> 00:17:06,204
they were stealing the greatest thing

347
00:17:06,204 --> 00:17:07,704
looked similar to the "pin" here!

348
00:17:07,704 --> 00:17:09,504
Of course they look similar.

349
00:17:09,504 --> 00:17:11,009
I had Officer Chiba

350
00:17:11,009 --> 00:17:13,011
copy the word "ip" and "pin"

351
00:17:13,204 --> 00:17:14,704
and just pasted them together.

352
00:17:14,704 --> 00:17:16,304
In other words,

353
00:17:16,304 --> 00:17:19,504
the chairman copied these same characters on the Japanese paper

354
00:17:19,504 --> 00:17:21,904
and showed them to you.

355
00:17:21,904 --> 00:17:23,904
He was looking for a person who would read this not as a number,

356
00:17:23,904 --> 00:17:26,004
but rather as the kanji character "pin".

357
00:17:26,004 --> 00:17:29,504
And, you flew right into the trap he set up.

358
00:17:29,504 --> 00:17:31,704
Don't be ridiculous.

359
00:17:31,704 --> 00:17:34,204
If you so insist,

360
00:17:34,204 --> 00:17:35,804
show us the Japanese paper!

361
00:17:35,804 --> 00:17:38,304
Do you know, sir?

362
00:17:38,304 --> 00:17:40,204
That Japanese paper is special

363
00:17:40,204 --> 00:17:42,704
and is made with the fallen leaves of a type of mulberry tree

364
00:17:42,704 --> 00:17:44,404
called a paper mulberry

365
00:17:44,404 --> 00:17:47,504
and is highly toxic.

366
00:17:47,504 --> 00:17:50,404
So, if you mistakenly lick it.

367
00:17:54,104 --> 00:17:56,304
Don't tell me that you...

368
00:17:57,404 --> 00:17:58,804
Ambulance.

369
00:17:58,804 --> 00:18:00,804
Please hurry and get me an ambulance!

370
00:18:00,804 --> 00:18:03,504
I ate that Japanese paper!

371
00:18:03,504 --> 00:18:05,404
Then, you admit it?

372
00:18:05,404 --> 00:18:07,804
That you got into a fight with the chairman over that paper,

373
00:18:07,804 --> 00:18:10,404
he fell down the stairs

374
00:18:10,404 --> 00:18:12,604
where you left him to die and you fled.

375
00:18:12,604 --> 00:18:15,073
Yeah, I admit it.

376
00:18:15,073 --> 00:18:18,004
I admit it, so hurry and call an ambulance!

377
00:18:18,004 --> 00:18:19,077
While you're at it,

378
00:18:19,077 --> 00:18:23,081
will you also admit that you're the head of the band of robbers?

379
00:18:23,081 --> 00:18:27,085
Right, it's me! I'm the head of "Hyakkiyako"!

380
00:18:27,085 --> 00:18:30,404
As soon as he walked into my waiting room,

381
00:18:30,404 --> 00:18:32,804
that old man while grinning said...

382
00:18:32,804 --> 00:18:35,093
Long time no see,

383
00:18:35,093 --> 00:18:41,099
the head of the band of robbers who killed my pet dog.

384
00:18:41,099 --> 00:18:43,404
I thought that you'd come back

385
00:18:43,404 --> 00:18:45,904
to get the hanging scroll of the wild boar

386
00:18:45,904 --> 00:18:48,304
that you failed to steal back then.

387
00:18:48,304 --> 00:18:50,604
But don't you worry.

388
00:18:50,604 --> 00:18:55,113
I may just forgive you depending how you decide to act.

389
00:18:55,304 --> 00:18:57,704
If you want to flee, I won't stop you.

390
00:18:57,704 --> 00:19:01,119
I'll simply report you to the police.

391
00:19:01,119 --> 00:19:05,604
I've got your face right inside my TV camera,

392
00:19:05,604 --> 00:19:09,127
so I've got this paper that'll serve as evidence too.

393
00:19:09,127 --> 00:19:12,104
Since... since he said that I thought I'd be in trouble,

394
00:19:12,104 --> 00:19:15,133
so I tried to snatch the paper away from him

395
00:19:15,133 --> 00:19:18,304
then the old man fell down the stairs.

396
00:19:18,304 --> 00:19:21,139
Therefore, you left the chairman there to die and fled.

397
00:19:21,139 --> 00:19:24,304
Then, you swallowed the paper to hide the evidence.

398
00:19:24,304 --> 00:19:27,504
Yeah! So, hurry and call an ambulance, will you?

399
00:19:27,504 --> 00:19:28,904
Or, I'll die!

400
00:19:28,904 --> 00:19:31,149
You'll be fine.

401
00:19:31,149 --> 00:19:34,004
Mulberry leaves are frequently used to make Japanese paper,

402
00:19:34,004 --> 00:19:36,204
and they're not that poisonous.

403
00:19:36,204 --> 00:19:38,404
What... what are you saying?

